<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM0000026VQ000X_07_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___00009W200000">
<testtitle>CHECK OTHER DTCS OUTPUT (IN ADDITION TO DTC P2808)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG) and turn the intelligent tester on.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the following items: "DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / DTC INFO / CURRENT CODES".</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Read the DTCs using the intelligent tester.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="3.83in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.25in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Display (DTC output)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Only "P2808" is output</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>A</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>"P2808" and other DTCs</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>B</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
<atten4>
<ptxt>If a solenoid is stuck OFF, DTCs for several solenoids including the malfunctioning solenoid will be detected.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM0000026VQ000X_07_0002" fin="false">B</down>
<right ref="RM0000026VQ000X_07_0003" fin="false">A</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM0000026VQ000X_07_0002" proc-id="RM0250U___00009W300000">
<testtitle>PERFORM ACTIVE TEST BY INTELLIGENT TESTER</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<ptxt>This test should always be performed with at least 2 people.</ptxt>
</atten3>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Start the engine and turn the intelligent tester on.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the following items: "DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / ECT / ACTIVE TEST / SHIFT".</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>While driving, the shift position can be forcibly changed with the intelligent tester.</ptxt>
<ptxt>Comparing the shift position commanded by the ACTIVE TEST with the actual shift position enables you to confirm the problem (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000O8L020X"/>). </ptxt>
